This is a Deno codebase and as such should strive to use Deno's built in functionality as much as possible.

This codebase will have EXCELENT test coverage. Any change should result in a new or updated test.

You must write tests one at a time and run them to ensure they pass before doing ANYTHING else. NEVER write more than one test at once.

This codebase will have EXCELENT documentation, and will follow Deno best practices with regard to documentation.

This codebase produces an application that allows playing music.

This codebase does not cut corners. NEVER do things like commiting/pushing with --no-verfiy or disabling tests.

## Coverage baseline

Tests enforce coverage against `coverage-baseline.json`. When you add or improve
tests, run `deno task coverage:baseline` and commit the updated
`coverage-baseline.json` with your changes. Do not lower the baseline; fix
regressions by adding tests or restoring code. See README [Coverage
section](../README.md#updating-the-baseline-during-development).

## UI

This codebase uses a custom HTML element approach to building UIs.

This codebase uses icons based on svg from https://heroicons.com

When adding a heroicon, verify the SVG path matches the official source before
claiming work is done. Fetch from unpkg (e.g.
`https://unpkg.com/@heroicons/react@2.1.1/24/outline/IconNameIcon.js`) and
compare the `d` attribute. Do not rely on memory or browser MCP for localhost.

The codebase uses standard CSS, no Tailwind classes.

Any global styling (eg: typography, spacing, utility classes used in multiple places) should be kept in app.css
